## Performance Considerations

### KaTeX Loading
Load KaTeX efficiently in [src/components/MathMarkdown.tsx](mdc:src/components/MathMarkdown.tsx):

```typescript
// Dynamic import for KaTeX
const loadKatex = async () => {
  const katex = await import('katex')
  return katex
}

// Cache rendered expressions
const mathCache = new Map<string, string>()
```

### Physics Calculation Caching
Cache expensive physics calculations:

```typescript
// Memoize physics solutions
const memoizedCalculation = useMemo(() => {
  return calculatePhysicsSolution(problemData)
}, [problemData])
```

## Accessibility for Math Content

### Screen Reader Support
Ensure mathematical content is accessible:

```typescript
// Provide alt text for math expressions
<span aria-label="E equals m c squared">
  <MathMarkdown content="\\( E = mc^2 \\)" />
</span>

// Use semantic markup
<div role="math" aria-label="Force equals mass times acceleration">
  \\[ F = ma \\]
</div>
```

### High Contrast Math
Ensure math expressions work in different themes:

```css
/* Math content styling */
.katex {
  color: inherit;
}

.katex .base {
  color: var(--foreground);
}
```